<br>
run3, regen3, scm3 and now working towards mgb.  I barely exp so I'm a slow one hehe.  Oh, and I have RC which is very useful. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=346877">Emmie</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morinkhanmt>MorinkhanMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Egging EW</span><br>  Posts: 465<br> <font color=#628CBC>(5/9/03 12:40:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what is the best path for aa's.</span><hr size=1> The two best AAs a cleric gets are SCM3 and DvA (at least L1). IMO, you should forget all other AAs until you have them. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:verdana;font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47567" target="top">Morinkhan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> | <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.furysedge.com">Fury's Edge</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Morell Thule</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pynkyand>pynkyand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#628CBC>(5/9/03 12:49:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what is the best path for aa's.</span><hr size=1> what is dva? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morinkhanmt>MorinkhanMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Egging EW</span><br>  Posts: 466<br> <font color=#628CBC>(5/9/03 1:21:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what is the best path for aa's.</span><hr size=1> Divine Arbitration<br>
<br>
It's a manaless, almost instacast, aggroless &quot;heal&quot;. It takes hps from all members of your group and balances them. If you had 5 members at 100% and one at 20%, you hit DvA and all 6 party members would almost instantly be at 80%. It hurts the full members, but heals the damaged one. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:verdana;font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47567" target="top">Morinkhan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> | <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.furysedge.com">Fury's Edge</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Morell Thule</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=crystilla>crystilla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Karnors</span><br>  Posts: 1072<br> <font color=#628CBC>(5/9/03 1:31:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what is the best path for aa's.</span><hr size=1> Here's a couple links from this board that we've discussed aa's.<br>
<br>
1)  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20?page=4">Average one, may have something interesting in here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
2)  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showMessage?topicID=58.topic">Really good one to read</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
However, the general theme I definitely agree with.<br>
<br>
The best AA's for clerics (regardless if you're a raid cleric or exp cleric) are SCM and Divine Arbitration.<br>
<br>
Think of SCM as a mana preservation item that is with you, even when you die.  It works on more than just heals.  It works all the time on every spell you cast (no level restriction).<br>
<br>
Divine Arbitration is an awesome no aggro re-adjustment of HP.  It saves that ranger coming in with a mob who got lucky, it helps save that chanter who got aggro early.  It helps save that warrior who got a bunch of procs cast on him, throwing off your timing.<br>
<br>
Healing gift and healing adept are good, but SCM is generally the route most clerics are strongly urged to get first.<br>
<br>
I was a cleric who didn't pay enough attention to others, so went with healing gift and mental clarity to get my 12 points so I could do MGB.  Then, I got DvA and then went back and got SCM.  I could kick myself because I didn't do SCM sooner.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pynkyand>pynkyand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#628CBC>(5/9/03 2:10:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what is the best path for aa's.</span><hr size=1> cool thanks allot. I was actually going to get my 12 points and then buy my 100% rez thing before i got my mgb. But from hearing everyone i guess i should get that first.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=crystilla>crystilla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Karnors</span><br>  Posts: 1073<br> <font color=#628CBC>(5/9/03 2:18:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what is the best path for aa's.</span><hr size=1> MGB (class aa's) is good but not always a necessity.  SCM (archtype aa's) is basically what we are suggesting most clerics should go for when they are first starting out.<br>
<br>
I have HG2 (had 3 points banked for HG3 so I could get divine rez, cel regen and bestow divine aura) but ended up ding'ing 63 so got DvA2 with those 3 points.  So, I'm back down to 1 banked now but saving for HG3 so I can go after those prerequisite ones myself.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morinkhanmt>MorinkhanMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Egging EW</span><br>  Posts: 467<br> <font color=#628CBC>(5/9/03 2:19:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what is the best path for aa's.</span><hr size=1> Divine Rez is nice... you come back with 100% xp, full mana and no rez effects... BUT... it's on a 36hr reuse timer. That's RL time, not game-time. So if you play evening only, you can only use it every 3rd day of playtime. I believe you also have to have HG3 to get DivRez.<br>
<br>
One last note on AAs in general... watch for the level restrictions. For example, you can't get DvA1 until L61. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:verdana;font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47567" target="top">Morinkhan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> | <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.furysedge.com">Fury's Edge</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Morell Thule</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pynkyand>pynkyand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#628CBC>(5/9/03 2:24:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what is the best path for aa's.</span><hr size=1> yhea you have to have hg 3 to get it i already bought 1 lev of hg which i wish i had not now but oh well. I am not in any guild so i figed that I really do not need mass group buff since i am only 56 and well lets face it everyone wants boa or higher cast on them and my hb does not cut it. so i figed that to cut back on time lost i can play if i happen to die once that die puff all xp back and rdy to go. then just leave my char selling all day to kill the timmer on it<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morinkhanmt>MorinkhanMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Egging EW</span><br>  Posts: 468<br> <font color=#628CBC>(5/9/03 3:42:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what is the best path for aa's.</span><hr size=1> Since it's 36 real-life hours, it doesn't matter if you're actually logged in or not. If I use DivRez at 9pm on Monday night, I can't use it again until 9am on Wednesday morning, no matter if my char is logged on or not.<br>
<br>
If you're not currently guilded and (I assume) not a heavy raider, I definitely think you should get AAs that improve your character directly, making you more desirable for xp groups.<br>
<br>
SCM3, DvA1 when you get to L61, HA/HG, maybe MC1. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:verdana;font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47567" target="top">Morinkhan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> | <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.furysedge.com">Fury's Edge</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Morell Thule</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pynkyand>pynkyand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Qeynos Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#628CBC>(5/9/03 4:14:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what is the best path for aa's.</span><hr size=1> I used to be a heavy raider but i took a 6mo leave of the game and found that the guild i was in disbaned so now i am kind of floating around getting pick up groups either in pod or seb. <br>
<br>
At this point i am kind of at a lost i guess mabey i should just get the aa points and hold off on spending them to see if i join a guild <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morinkhanmt>MorinkhanMT</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Egging EW</span><br>  Posts: 469<br> <font color=#628CBC>(5/9/03 4:49:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what is the best path for aa's.</span><hr size=1> Well, you can definitely start banking AA points if you want, but also consider just plain levelling up. Unless you have a specific reason to stay at L56, there are an awful lot of benefits to getting L63-65.<br>
<br>
Plus there are level restrictions on AA abilities too, so you'd have to level up anyway before you could spend any AA points you save up. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:verdana;font-size:xx-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47567" target="top">Morinkhan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> | <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.furysedge.com">Fury's Edge</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Morell Thule</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=crystilla>crystilla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Karnors</span><br>  Posts: 1075<br> <font color=#628CBC>(5/9/03 5:16:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=158.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: what is the best path for aa's.</span><hr size=1> Aye, forgot the level issue.<br>
<br>
If you want to do aa's and level (cover your ears naysayers lol), you could do the following.<br>
<br>
Put about 10-20% to aa and the rest to leveling; that equals about half total experience going to aa and the other half to leveling.  That way, you can earn some aa's but also get the needed levels.<br>
<br>
At 56, there are not a lot of aa's that would help you immensely other than SCM.  For one reason, getting HA or HG maxxed may mean more aggro chances for you and depending where you're fighting, that can be dangerous.<br>
<br>
I started aa's when I hit lvl 54, and when I hit 60, I had somewhere between 8-12 of them.  Unless I was within those last few percentage points of a level or aa ding, I always had 20% going to AA all the way from lvl 54 to 60.  So, it's an option for you if you want.<br>
<br>
